The paper discusses a scalable algorithm for learning Support Vector Machines (SVMs) in a distributed setting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of primal and dual formulations of the problem, which are common in optimization (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of SVMs for classification problems, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
